decks.notes: The main idea of this deck is to quickly flood the board with cheap artifacts and use cards like Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Thoughtcast to draw more cards and maintain momentum. The deck also includes removal and disruption cards like Tormod's Crypt and Sink into Stupor to control the game and prevent opponents from establishing a strong board presence. Urza's Saga and Engineered Explosives provide additional utility and flexibility in dealing with threats. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a fast and aggressive playstyle fueled by efficient artifact synergies.

This UW Control deck focuses on controlling the board through countering spells, board wipes, and removal while utilizing powerful Planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler and Narset, Parter of Veils to generate card advantage and control the game. The inclusion of Isochron Scepter and powerful instant spells like Orim's Chant and Prismatic Ending provide additional ways to control the board efficiently. The deck also includes a Companion, Kaheera, the Orphanguard, to provide additional synergy and support for the main game plan of outlasting opponents and winning through attrition.

This deck focuses on using aggressive creatures to quickly chip away at the opponent's life total while disrupting their game plan with cards like Fatal Push and Teferi, Time Raveler. The deck also includes powerful creatures like Elesh Norn, Mother of Machines to further overwhelm the opponent. The key strategy is to maintain control of the board with efficient removal spells and disruptive creatures, while also applying pressure with aggressive threats to quickly close out the game.

This deck focuses on aggressive creature-based plays with a mix of control elements. It aims to quickly establish a board presence with creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd, while using interaction like Prismatic Ending and Consign to Memory to control the opponent's board. Utilizing powerful enchantments like Fable of the Mirror-Breaker and Arena of Glory, as well as versatile removal spells like Solitude and Galvanic Discharge, this deck aims to maintain pressure on the opponent while disrupting their game plan.

This Dimir Control deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan using a combination of spells like Thoughtseize, Counterspell, and Fatal Push, along with creatures like Murktide Regent and Kaito, Bane of Nightmares. The deck also includes card draw and selection tools like Preordain and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student to ensure the player has the right answers at the right time. The deck aims to control the game through tempo advantage and card advantage, eventually overwhelming the opponent with powerful threats and efficient removal spells.

This deck focuses on controlling the game by disrupting the opponent's strategy with a mix of counterspells, hand disruption, and removal spells. The key strategy is to outvalue the opponent by efficiently using cards like Teferi, Time Raveler and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student to draw cards and generate advantage. The deck also includes powerful creatures like Solitude and Subtlety to deal with threats on the board. By carefully managing resources and controlling the pace of the game, this deck aims to outlast the opponent and win through attrition.

The deck focuses on utilizing combo pieces to quickly bring back powerful creatures from the graveyard using instant speed effects. It aims to disrupt opponents with discard spells like Thoughtseize while also maintaining flexibility with removal spells like Fatal Push and Prismatic Ending. The main win condition is to reanimate creatures like Griselbrand with Goryo's Vengeance and protect them with counter magic like Force of Negation. This deck thrives on tempo plays and being able to combo off quickly to overwhelm opponents with powerful threats.

This deck focuses on generating a large amount of mana quickly through cards like Ruby Medallion and rituals, then casting multiple spells in a single turn to deal massive damage with cards like Ral, Monsoon Mage and Grapeshot. The deck also utilizes cards like Wish and Past in Flames to recur key spells and maintain consistency. Overall, the key concept of this deck is to quickly assemble the combo pieces needed to create a storm of spells and overwhelm the opponent in a short amount of time.

The deck focuses on quickly filling the graveyard with powerful creatures like Griselbrand and then bringing them back to the battlefield with cards like Goryo's Vengeance. The combination of control elements like Thoughtseize and Force of Negation along with reanimation effects allows the deck to quickly assemble a powerful board state and disrupt the opponent's game plan. Additionally, the deck includes cards like Solitude and Faithful Mending for added versatility and protection. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a powerful creature while maintaining control of the game.

The deck focuses on controlling the board and slowing down the opponent's game plan through a mix of removal spells, counter spells, and versatile creatures. It aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy while building up its own resources and card advantage. The deck includes powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Time Raveler, and utilizes powerful creatures like Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd and Solitude to stabilize the board. With access to a variety of versatile spells and powerful creatures, the deck aims to outvalue and outlast its opponents in longer games.

This deck focuses on quickly building up a board presence and putting pressure on the opponent with low-cost, aggressive creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Slickshot Show-Off. It utilizes cheap spells like Lava Dart and Lightning Bolt to control the board and deal damage to the opponent. The deck also includes card draw and deck manipulation spells like Expressive Iteration and Preordain to ensure consistency in drawing the right cards. Overall, the deck aims to win the game quickly by overwhelming the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells.

This deck focuses on aggressively playing creatures and controlling the board with spells such as Lightning Bolt and Leyline Binding. It utilizes powerful creatures like Territorial Kavu, Scion of Draco, and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury to quickly deal damage to the opponent. The deck also includes cards like Consign to Memory and Arena of Glory to provide additional control and card advantage. By combining aggressive creatures with disruptive spells, the deck aims to quickly overwhelm the opponent and secure a fast victory.

This deck focuses on aggressive plays using a combination of mana-efficient creatures and powerful spells to quickly overwhelm opponents. The deck utilizes a diverse mana base to enable the casting of a variety of powerful threats, including Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, and Scion of Draco. Leyline Binding and Leyline of the Guildpact provide additional support and protection for your creatures, while Lightning Bolt and Stubborn Denial help control the board and protect your game plan. Consign to Memory offers a versatile removal option, while Doorkeeper Thrull provides a late-game win condition. Teferi, Time Raveler and Winternight Stories offer additional utility and versatility to the deck.

The main concept of this Boros Aggro deck is to quickly overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and powerful abilities. The deck focuses on utilizing efficient cards like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah, Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, and Guide of Souls to quickly apply pressure to the opponent. Cards like Goblin Bombardment and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury provide additional reach and damage potential. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Blood Moon and Elegant Parlor to disrupt the opponent's game plan. Overall, the deck aims to be fast-paced and proactive in securing a victory.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy through hand disruption spells like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek while applying early pressure with efficient creatures like Thought-Knot Seer and Nethergoyf. Mishra's Bauble helps to manipulate the top of the library for better draws, and cards like Fatal Push and Kozilek's Command serve as versatile removal spells. The deck also includes a small Eldrazi package with cards like Emperor of Bones and Eldrazi Temple to provide additional threats and mana ramp. Overall, the deck aims to control the game tempo and close out matches quickly through a combination of disruption and aggression.

This deck aims to quickly ramp up mana using Amulet of Vigor and Green Sun's Zenith to summon powerful creatures like Primeval Titan. The goal is to tutor for key lands like Urza's Saga and Boseiju, Who Endures to establish a strong board presence. With the ability to generate massive amounts of mana, the deck can quickly overwhelm opponents with powerful plays like Scapeshift and Lotus Field. The deck also includes some utility lands like Mirrorpool and Hanweir Battlements to provide additional flexibility and options in different matchups.
